JS if else:

- Use the else statement to specify a block of code to be executed if a condition is false.
- syntax:
            if (condition) {
                // code to execute if the condition is true
            } else {
                // code to execute if the condition is false
            }

- eg, If the hour is less than 18, create a "Good day" greeting, otherwise "Good evening":

    let currentHour = new Date().getHours();
    if(currentHour < 18){
        document.getElementById("message").innerHTML = "Good day!";
    } else {
        document.getElementById("message").innerHTML = "Good evening!";
    }